Privacy Policy for ezFlowcuz
Effective Date: March 25, 2026

1. Introduction
Welcome to ezFlowcuz (“the App”). This Privacy Policy explains how we handle your information when you use our App. We are committed to protecting your privacy.

2. Data Collection and Storage
ezFlowcuz does not collect, transmit, or upload any personal data to external servers. All data generated by your use of the App is stored locally on your device only, using the Hive database. This data includes:

Settings: App preferences such as first‑launch status, dark/light mode, and language selection (e.g., if you choose German, the App remembers this for your next session).

Tasks & Habits: Your to‑do tasks, once tasks, habits, and related items.

Categories: Custom categories you create for organizing tasks and habits.

Timer Data: Selected timer presets and timer duration records.

Statistics: Historical data about your habits, categories, monthly habit records, and once tasks.

All this information remains on your device. You have full control and can delete it at any time by clearing the App’s data in your device settings or uninstalling the App.

3. Permissions
To provide its core functionality and display advertisements, ezFlowcuz requires the following permissions:

Internet Access: Used to load ads from third‑party ad networks. No personal data is transmitted to our own servers.

Advertising ID: Ad networks may access your device’s advertising identifier to serve relevant ads. You can reset this ID or limit ad tracking in your device’s privacy settings.

4. Third‑Party Services
We use third‑party advertising services that may collect certain information to provide and improve ads. These services include:

Google AdMob

MobFox

These third parties may automatically collect data such as:

Device information (model, operating system version, advertising ID)

IP address and network connection type

App usage related to ads (e.g., ad views, clicks)

Approximate location (based on IP address or if location permission is granted)

This data is collected and processed by Google AdMob and MobFox according to their own privacy policies. We do not have access to or control over the data these third parties collect.

Your Choices:
You can reset your advertising ID or enable “Limit Ad Tracking” (iOS) / “Opt out of Ads Personalization” (Android) in your device settings. For users in the European Economic Area (EEA), the UK, or other regions with similar requirements, these ad networks may present a consent dialog to manage tracking preferences.

Google AdMob Privacy Policy: https://policies.google.com/privacy

MobFox Privacy Policy: https://www.mobfox.com/privacy-policy/

5. Data Security & User Control
Because all user‑generated data remains locally on your device, its security relies on the built‑in protections of your operating system and device. You can delete all your data at any time by:

Going to your device’s system settings, selecting the App, and tapping “Clear Data.”

Uninstalling the App.

For data processed by third‑party ad networks, those services implement industry‑standard security measures.

6. Children’s Privacy
The App does not knowingly collect any personal data from children under 13. If you are a parent or guardian and believe your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us so we can take appropriate action.

7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time. Any changes will be posted within the App or on this page, and the “Effective Date” will be updated accordingly.

